    "pathophysiology": [
      "Most commonly spreads from ethmoid sinusitis via lamina papyracea (thin medial orbital wall)",
      "Preseptal: anterior to orbital septum — no proptosis or EOM restriction",
      "Postseptal: violates septum, involves orbital fat and extraocular muscles",
      "Subperiosteal abscess forms between periorbita and bone; intraconal abscess compresses optic nerve",
      "Increased orbital pressure causes optic nerve ischemia and vision loss",
      "Intracranial extension via superior orbital fissure risks cavernous sinus thrombosis"
